<abstract abstract-type="short" xml:lang="en"><p><![CDATA[Abstract The article introduces one of Paulo Freire&#8217;s most important and best known books. The author analyzes in depth the context and the issues from which emerge the central ideas of the proposals for a popular education committed to the needs of the poorest.]]></p></abstract>
